#: ../../E/epsilon-squared.rst:5
msgid "epsilon squared"
msgstr "epsilon squared"

#: ../../E/epsilon-squared.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../E/epsilon-squared.rst:9
msgid ""
"A quantity even smaller than :ref:`epsilon`\\, as small in comparison to "
"epsilon as epsilon is to something normal; completely negligible. If you buy"
" a supercomputer for a million dollars, the cost of the thousand-dollar "
"terminal to go with it is :ref:`epsilon`\\, and the cost of the ten-dollar "
"cable to connect them is epsilon squared. Compare :ref:`lost-in-the-"
"underflow`\\, :ref:`lost-in-the-noise`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`epsilon`\\ "
"よりさらに小さい量で、epsilonがふつうの何かに対して小さいのと同じくらい、epsilonに対して小さいもの。完全に無視できる。百万ドルでスーパーコンピューターを買うなら、それに付ける千ドルの端末の費用は\\"
" :ref:`epsilon`\\ であり、それらをつなぐ10ドルのケーブルの費用はepsilon squaredである。\\ :ref:`lost-"
"in-the-underflow`\\ 、\\ :ref:`lost-in-the-noise`\\ と比較せよ。"
